    </div>
    <a href="/quiz" class="btn-p" style="padding:0.6rem 1.25rem;font-size:0.78rem;">Take the Gap Assessment →</a>
  </div>
</nav>

<div class="hero">
  <div class="hero-inner">
    <div class="badge"><span class="badge-dot"></span>Free calculator · 90 seconds</div>
    <h1 class="hero-h">Fractional CMO ROI <em style="color:#00C853;font-style:italic;">calculator.</em></h1>
    <p class="hero-sub">
      Adjust the inputs to your situation. The calculator compares year-one all-in cost and likely outcome across three options: fractional CMO, full-time CMO hire, and founder-led DIY. Calibrated to 2026 market benchmarks.
    </p>
  </div>
</div>

<section>
  <div class="sec-inner">
    <div class="calc-inputs">
      <span class="lbl">Your inputs</span>

      <div class="field">
        <label for="company-stage">Company stage / revenue</label>
        <span class="helper">Affects the realistic comp range and ROI expectations</span>
        <select id="company-stage">
          <option value="seed">Pre-PMF / Seed ($0–$2M)</option>
          <option value="early" selected>Early growth ($2M–$10M)</option>
          <option value="growth">Growth stage ($10M–$30M)</option>
          <option value="scale">Scaling ($30M–$75M)</option>
        </select>
      </div>

      <div class="field">
        <label for="ceo-hours">CEO hours per week currently on marketing decisions</label>
        <span class="helper">Marketing strategy, campaign approvals, agency oversight, content review — anything marketing-related</span>
        <div class="slider-row">
          <input type="range" id="ceo-hours" min="0" max="30" value="12" />
          <span class="slider-val" id="ceo-hours-val">12 hrs</span>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="field">
        <label for="ceo-cost">CEO loaded hourly cost ($)</label>
        <span class="helper">Founder salary + dilution + opportunity cost — typical founders: $250–$500/hr</span>
        <div class="slider-row">
          <input type="range" id="ceo-cost" min="150" max="800" step="25" value="350" />
          <span class="slider-val" id="ceo-cost-val">$350/hr</span>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="field">
        <label for="fractional-hours">Fractional CMO hours per month (preferred)</label>
        <span class="helper">Typical: 20–40 hours/month. Lower for advisory, higher for embedded operator.</span>
        <div class="slider-row">
          <input type="range" id="fractional-hours" min="10" max="40" value="25" />
          <span class="slider-val" id="fractional-hours-val">25 hrs</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <span class="lbl">Year-one comparison</span>
    <div class="compare-grid">

      <div class="opt-card" id="card-fractional">
        <div class="opt-tag" id="fractional-tag">—</div>
        <div class="opt-name">Fractional CMO</div>
        <div class="opt-cost" id="frac-cost">$120K</div>
        <div class="opt-cost-label">Year-one all-in</div>
        <div class="opt-row"><span>Monthly fee</span><span id="frac-monthly">$10K</span></div>
        <div class="opt-row"><span>Setup &amp; onboarding</span><span>—</span></div>
        <div class="opt-row"><span>Equity dilution</span><span>None</span></div>
        <div class="opt-row"><span>Recruiter fee</span><span>None</span></div>
        <div class="opt-row"><span>Notice period</span><span>30 days</span></div>
        <div class="opt-row"><span>Hours/month</span><span id="frac-hrs">25 hrs</span></div>
      </div>

      <div class="opt-card" id="card-fulltime">
        <div class="opt-tag" id="ft-tag">—</div>
        <div class="opt-name">Full-time CMO</div>
        <div class="opt-cost" id="ft-cost">$520K</div>
        <div class="opt-cost-label">Year-one all-in</div>
        <div class="opt-row"><span>Base + variable</span><span id="ft-base">$375K</span></div>
        <div class="opt-row"><span>Benefits</span><span>$45K</span></div>
        <div class="opt-row"><span>Equity (1–2% est. value)</span><span id="ft-equity">$50K+</span></div>
        <div class="opt-row"><span>Recruiter fee</span><span>$75K</span></div>
        <div class="opt-row"><span>Notice period</span><span>3–9 mo</span></div>
        <div class="opt-row"><span>Hours/month</span><span>~160 hrs</span></div>
      </div>

      <div class="opt-card" id="card-diy">
        <div class="opt-tag" id="diy-tag">—</div>
        <div class="opt-name">CEO-led (DIY)</div>
        <div class="opt-cost" id="diy-cost">$218K</div>
        <div class="opt-cost-label">CEO opportunity cost</div>
        <div class="opt-row"><span>CEO hours/year on marketing</span><span id="diy-hrs">624 hrs</span></div>
        <div class="opt-row"><span>CEO hourly cost</span><span id="diy-hourly">$350/hr</span></div>
        <div class="opt-row"><span>Equity dilution</span><span>None</span></div>
        <div class="opt-row"><span>Recruiter fee</span><span>None</span></div>
        <div class="opt-row"><span>Notice period</span><span>n/a</span></div>
        <div class="opt-row"><span>Strategic expertise</span><span>Limited</span></div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="verdict">
      <h3 id="verdict-h">Recommended for your stage: Fractional CMO</h3>
      <p id="verdict-p">For early growth companies ($2M–$10M), the fractional model captures the senior strategic value of a CMO without the dilution, recruiter risk, or 9-month onboarding ramp. Switch to full-time when you cross $25M–$30M and the function genuinely requires 40+ hours/week of leadership.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section>
  <div class="sec-inner">
    <span class="lbl">How the math works</span>
    <h2 class="h2">What's behind the calculation</h2>
    <p class="body"><strong style="color:#F0FFF0;">Fractional cost</strong> = monthly fee × 12. The default monthly fee scales with the requested hours/month (using $400/hr blended rate as a benchmark).</p>
    <p class="body"><strong style="color:#F0FFF0;">Full-time cost</strong> includes base + variable + benefits + equity-value + recruiter fee, scaled to your stage. Equity value is estimated at the midpoint of typical CMO grants (1–2% of company value at next round).</p>
    <p class="body"><strong style="color:#F0FFF0;">DIY (CEO-led) cost</strong> = (CEO hrs/week × 52) × CEO hourly cost. This is the <em>opportunity cost</em> of CEO time spent on marketing rather than on CEO-level work. Most CEOs significantly underestimate this number.</p>
    <p class="body">For the deeper analysis of when each fits, see <a href="/fractional-cmo-vs-full-time-cmo" style="color:#00C853;text-decoration:none;">fractional CMO vs. full-time CMO</a> and <a href="/signs-you-need-a-fractional-cmo" style="color:#00C853;text-decoration:none;">signs you need a fractional CMO</a>.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<section>
  <div class="sec-inner">
    <span class="lbl">Related</span>
    <h2 class="h2">Related calculators &amp; resources</h2>
    <ul style="list-style:none;padding:0;color:#C0D8C0;font-size:0.95rem;line-height:1.85;">
      <li style="padding:0.5rem 0;border-bottom:1px solid #1A3A1A;"><a href="/ai-roi-calculator" style="color:#00C853;text-decoration:none;">AI ROI calculator →</a></li>
